# Local Dev Diary

After meaningful work, append a concise entry to the local diary only when diary capture is enabled.

First check for `~/.config/qvac-pr-skills/diary.enabled`. If it is missing, do nothing and do not mention diary logging.

Log after substantive work:

- PR review or PR feedback
- PR testing or validation
- Coding, debugging, investigation, docs, release work, triage, comms, blockers
- Any other substantive work the user asked for

Do not log casual questions, orientation-only file reading, config lookup, or tool setup with no work outcome.

Use the repo helper when available:

```bash
node .cursor/skills/_lib/developer-workflow/diary-cli.mjs --append '<json-entry>'
```

Entry JSON shape:

```json
{
  "title": "Short activity title",
  "summary": "One or two lines describing outcome.",
  "type": "pr-review | pr-testing | coding | release | investigation | docs | triage | comms | blocker | other",
  "ticket": "optional ticket id",
  "pr": "optional PR number",
  "status": "done | wip | blocked",
  "blocker": "optional blocker detail"
}
```

Keep entries short. Never write diary files into the repo.
